### Example 1: Get Public Properties

This example shows you how to get the public properties of a class.

```php
$props = get_class_properties(ExampleClass::class);
var_dump($props);
```
The code above produces this output on PHP v5.6.30, PHP v7.0.20, PHP v7.1.6:

```
array(2) {
  ["value1"]=>
  string(25) "I am public static value1"
  ["trait1"]=>
  string(25) "I am public static trait1"
}
```
